SUMMARY: Senate Minority Leader Mitch McConnell has returned to the Senate following a period of recovery in the wake of a fall.

TITLE: How to protect your portfolio, according to 3 investors
SUMMARY: Wall Street has been hit with a barrage of complex signals about the economy's health over the past month. From banking turmoil to weakening jobs data to slowing inflation, and now the start of earnings season, investors have remained largely resilient.

TITLE: Americans are struggling to pay off their car loans. Three charts explain why
SUMMARY: You've managed to buy the car, but can you afford to keep paying for it?

TITLE: Double delight for Kenya as Evans Chebet and Hellen Obiri win men's and women's Boston Marathon races
SUMMARY: There was double delight for Kenya at the 2023 Boston Marathon as Evans Chebet and Hellen Obiri won the men's and women's races respectively.

TITLE: McDonald's is upgrading its burgers
SUMMARY: McDonald's, which has been focusing on upgrading its core items to boost sales, is rolling out a series of changes designed to improve its signature burgers.

TITLE: Google-parent stock drops on fears it could lose search market share to AI-powered rivals
SUMMARY: Shares of Google-parent Alphabet fell more than 3% in early trading Monday after a report sparked concerns that its core search engine could lose market share to AI-powered rivals, including Microsoft's Bing.

TITLE: Tennessee Air National Guardsman applied to be a hitman online, the FBI says. It was a spoof website and now he's facing charges
SUMMARY: A Tennessee Air National Guardsman is facing charges after applying to be a hitman on a spoof "rent-a-hitman" website, according to the Department of Justice.

TITLE: FBI arrests two alleged Chinese agents and charges dozens with working inside US to silence dissidents
SUMMARY: The FBI has arrested two alleged Chinese agents and federal prosecutors have charged dozens of others with working to silence and harass dissidents within the United States -- with some even operating an "undeclared police station" in New York City.

TITLE: He was free for 2 years. Now Crosley Green is back in prison for a crime he says he didn't commit
SUMMARY: A Florida man who served three decades behind bars for a murder he says he didn't commit returned to prison Monday after spending the past two years building a life outside prison walls.

TITLE: Family of victim and survivors of Indianapolis FedEx mass shooting file lawsuit against gun magazine manufacturer and distributors
SUMMARY: The family of a victim and several survivors of a mass shooting at a FedEx facility in Indianapolis filed a lawsuit against companies involved in the manufacturing, marketing and sale of the high capacity magazine used by the gunman who killed 8 people and injured several others in 2021.

TITLE: Substitute teacher fired after she 'encouraged students to fight each other,' Texas school district says
SUMMARY: A substitute teacher in north Texas was fired after she "encouraged students to fight each other during class," the Mesquite Independent School District said.

TITLE: Fetterman returns to the Senate following treatment for clinical depression
SUMMARY: Sen. John Fetterman has returned to the Senate after receiving treatment for clinical depression at Walter Reed National Military Medical Center. The Pennsylvania Democrat began inpatient treatment in February and was discharged at the end of March.

TITLE: Speaker McCarthy lays out GOP debt limit plan in Wall Street visit
SUMMARY: Speaker Kevin McCarthy on Monday previewed what he hopes House Republicans can pass in the next few weeks to raise the debt ceiling during a speech at the New York Stock Exchange.

TITLE: Member of chatroom where leaked Pentagon documents surfaced tells CNN alleged leaker didn't want users to be 'shocked by news cycles'
SUMMARY: A member of the private online chatroom where a major leak of US classified documents surfaced has defended 21-year-old Jack Teixeira, who was charged in connection to the leak on Friday, telling CNN that Teixeira shared the classified material to keep other members informed, "so we won't be shocked by the news cycles."

TITLE: Clarence Thomas to amend financial disclosure forms to reflect sale to GOP megadonor
SUMMARY: Justice Clarence Thomas intends to amend his financial disclosure forms to reflect a 2014 real estate deal he made with a GOP megadonor -- an acknowledgment that the transaction should have been disclosed almost a decade ago, a source close to Thomas tells CNN.

TITLE: China's economy is off to a solid start, rising 4.5% in Q1 2023
SUMMARY: China's economy is off to a solid start in 2023 following its emergence from three years of strict pandemic restrictions.

TITLE: 5th grader raises $2,000 for grieving teacher
McCarthy makes plea for Republicans to back debt ceiling plan
SUMMARY: Speaker Kevin McCarthy made a plea to House Republicans during a closed-door meeting Tuesday morning to back his debt ceiling plan, telling them that although it doesn't have to include everything they want, it will help get him to the negotiating table.

TITLE: Democratic congressman has surgery to remove cancerous tumor in his tonsil
SUMMARY: Democratic Rep. Dan Kildee of Michigan had surgery Monday to remove a small cancerous tumor in his tonsil, his office said.

TITLE: Fulton County, Georgia, jail leadership resigns after inmate's death and accusations of unsanitary conditions
SUMMARY: Three officials at the Fulton County, Georgia, jail have stepped down amid an investigation into the death of an inmate whose family said was housed in a filthy, bug-infested cell that "was not fit for a diseased animal."

TITLE: Supreme Court seems sympathetic to postal worker who didn't work Sundays in dispute over religious accommodations
SUMMARY: The Supreme Court seemed to side with a former mail carrier, an evangelical Christian, who says the US Postal Service failed to accommodate his request to not work on Sundays.

TITLE: Biden will sign executive order aimed at expanding access to long-term care and child care
SUMMARY: President Joe Biden will sign an executive order in the Rose Garden Tuesday aimed at bolstering the "care economy," the White House said, issuing more than 50 directives across nearly every Cabinet-level agency in an effort to expand access to long-term care and child care.

TITLE: Fact check: Trump falsely claims Putin didn't boast of Russia's nuclear might during Trump presidency
SUMMARY: Former President Donald Trump has tried to mount an argument that he was a formidable deterrent to Russian President Vladimir Putin, the foreign leader Trump has for years been criticized for praising and defending. But Trump has been making a demonstrably false claim to support his case.

TITLE: GOP prepared to block vote to replace Feinstein on Senate Judiciary
SUMMARY: Senate Majority Leader Chuck Schumer said on Tuesday that he hopes to replace Democratic Sen. Dianne Feinstein on the Senate Judiciary Committee with Sen. Ben Cardin of Maryland and aims to set up a floor vote on the issue this afternoon, which Republicans are expected to block.

TITLE: Anti-abortion doctors urge Supreme Court to keep mifepristone restrictions in place
SUMMARY: A group of doctors opposed to abortion asked the Supreme Court Tuesday to restrict access to a key medication abortion drug while other legal challenges play out, as Wednesday night's deadline for the court to act approaches.

TITLE: McCarthy makes plea for Republicans to back debt ceiling plan
SUMMARY: Speaker Kevin McCarthy made a plea to House Republicans during a closed-door meeting Tuesday morning to back his debt ceiling plan, telling them that although it doesn't have to include everything they want, it will help get him to the negotiating table with President Joe Biden.
